## The quality gate

The credential-free gate is the repository's `pre-commit` hooks:

```bash
uvx pre-commit run --all-files
```

The base layer contributes:

- **Universal hygiene** — trailing-whitespace, end-of-file, YAML/TOML validity, merge-conflict
  markers, large-file guard, and secret scanning (gitleaks).
- **Governance enforcement** (language-agnostic) — Actions are SHA-pinned, `LICENSE` is verbatim
  Apache-2.0, root Markdown is allow-listed, and every `docs/` knowledge artefact carries
  enum-valid frontmatter.

A stack overlay adds its own lint, type-check, structure-lint, and test hooks. Run the same gate
locally that CI runs; CI is the backstop the local hook cannot be `--no-verify`'d past.

## Governance standards

This repository is built to externally maintained standards, referenced **by name only** (read the
canonical documents; do not expect their bodies inline):

- **repo-structure-standard** — the canonical directory layout for the stack.
- **repo-hygiene** — the mechanical enforcement layer (frontmatter, file placement, clean-repo
  rules) that the gates and pre-commit hooks operationalise.
- **governance-standards** — code-quality standards (typing, error handling, output contracts,
  idempotency).

When a convention seems arbitrary, its rationale lives in one of those three documents.

## Conventions (universal)

- **SHA-pinned GitHub Actions** — every `uses:` in `.github/workflows/` is pinned to a full commit
  SHA, not a moving tag (supply-chain integrity over convenience; see `docs/adr/`).
- **`docs/` frontmatter** — every Markdown file under `docs/` carries enum-valid YAML frontmatter
  (a recognised `type`/`status` set, per repo-hygiene). Files missing or carrying invalid
  frontmatter fail the gate.
- **Root Markdown allowlist** — only the OSS-furniture Markdown set lives at the repo root;
  everything else belongs under `docs/`.

